Text: Rose gazes at the sky from her room.

I was able to keep my mother safe by promising to wed
Perv. But now the fate of the kingdom is...

Shadow Garden is taking action. A traitor like myself
is likely no longer even an afterthought for them...
And then there is the Cult of Diablos to consider...

In the not so distant future, this land will become
the stage where those two forces collide...
But for now, all I can do is—
It can't be...
Rose opens the window and breaks into a run.
Cid!!!
That was pretty rough without magic...
Oh, hey Rose.

Before her stands the boy she has been pining after.
It's like a dream come true. She'd truly believed
they would never meet again.
Cid... Oh, Cid! How I've missed you!
Same here. I just had to see you.
There's something I have to tell you.
*gasp*!
Come inside, quickly! If anyone sees you—
But...how exactly did you get in the castle...?

I snuck in posing as the student of this pianist I
know.
You did all that for me...?
I need to talk about you getting married.
What could you possibly have to say?!
It's all a big lie, right?
One look in his eyes tells Rose how he feels.

He wants her to deny it, to tell him that she's not
marrying Perv, that he's the one she truly wants to
wed.

It was precisely because she loves Cid that she had
to push him away. Because they will never be
together. Because she could never put his life in
danger.
...It's not a lie. I'm going to marry Perv Asshat.
No!!!
C'mon, think about that day!
Don't you remember what you said?! That you'd—
Cid!!!
Please... Forget that day...and all about me...
Rose—
I refuse.
We're the same, don't you see?!

You became a dark knight, here in a land where people
scorn swordplay. You must have been so alone,
rejected by those around you, misunderstood by all.

But you stuck to your path in life. That's how we're
the same...
You and I...?
I have a dream that no one else understands, too.
That's why I know how you feel better than anyone.
Cid... Your dream is—
Rose knows what it is Cid dreams of.

No words are necessary, since it is a vision they both
share.
His dream is her dream, just as her dream is his.
—A dream that they be joined in holy matrimony.

Marrying the princess of the Oriana Kingdom is an
impossibility for a low-ranking noble, a dream too
ridiculous to say out loud.

And yet these feelings of Cid's are the one thing
Rose would never disavow, for they are proof of the
love between them.

I...I understand your dream! Everyone else may spurn
it, but not me...
The world doesn't think that way, though.

They call me a fool, call me crazy, tell me that it's
time to grow up...

No matter what anyone says, your dream is more
precious than anything in this world!
Rose...

We have tried to live life in our own way. Through
all the hurdles, all the scorn, we have persevered.
Only now, you've lost your way!
L-Lost my way...?!
You stabbed your betrothed and killed your father!

I won't ask why. I have faith that it was a choice
you made out of your conviction to stay true to
your path.
So why is it that you're trying to stray now?

Marrying someone you stabbed is the very definition
of compromising your goals!
You've stayed true for so long! Why give up now?!

Rose understands better than anyone that this is not
the life she wishes for herself.
...There's nothing more to say.
Please forget about me and live a happy life.
No! I need you...!
That...is all I ask.
I will marry Perv Asshat.
I received a report that voices were heard here.
Do you see anyone else?
...Hmph.
I see you've been crying.
Do not touch me.

This attitude of yours will not do. We are to be
husband and wife, after all.
Only...in...name—
I would mind that tongue of yours if I were you.

Don't forget that Queen Reina's life depends upon
your behavior.
*gasp*!
...I understand.
Very good.

Now come, we have a meeting about the ceremony to
attend.
...I understand.
I get it now... They've taken her mother hostage.
Maybe it's time to switch to plan B.
At any rate,
what if this here turns out to be the wedding ring?
I really put poor Perv in a fix...
